---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Series | Amid the Noise">

  <section class="section">
    <h1>Series</h1>
    <p>
      Multi-part work designed to unfold across systems, not just publish individual ideas.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- SERIES I -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <section class="section">

    <p class="series-label">Series I</p>
    <h2>Human-Governed Intelligence Systems</h2>
    <p class="series-description">
      A five-part framework for governing AI-mediated intelligence systems under conditions of ambiguity, pressure, and risk.
    </p>

    <div class="series-list">

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.1</p>
        <h3><a href="/papers/toward-a-human-governed-intelligence-infrastructure/">Toward a Human-Governed Intelligence Infrastructure</a></h3>
        <p>Establishes the case for treating AI-enabled intelligence systems as governed infrastructure, not passive tools.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.2</p>
        <h3><a href="/papers/operational-empathy-as-intelligence-capability/">Operational Empathy as Intelligence Capability</a></h3>
        <p>Reframes human context as a core capability for interpretation under ambiguity and incomplete signal.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.3</p>
        <h3><a href="/papers/the-civic-signal/">The Civic Signal</a></h3>
        <p>Positions trust, sentiment, and engagement as measurable inputs that shape intelligence outcomes.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.4</p>
        <h3><a href="/papers/signal-integrity/">Signal Integrity</a></h3>
        <p>Defines governance mechanisms to detect drift, resist distortion, and maintain alignment with reality.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <p class="item-number">I.5</p>
        <h3><a href="/papers/designed-lives/">Designed Lives</a></h3>
        <p>Translates system design into human consequence, showing how intelligence systems shape lived experience.</p>
      </article>

    </div>

  </section>

  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- TRANSITION -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <section class="section">
    <p class="series-transition">
      This series defines the system. The next puts it under load.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- SERIES II -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <section class="section">

    <p class="series-label">Series II</p>
    <h2>From Framework to Fielding</h2>
    <p class="series-description">
      Applies the framework in operational environments, where governance must hold under real-world constraints.
    </p>

    <p class="coming-soon">
      Forthcoming.
    </p>

  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .section {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .section + .section {
    border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  }

  .series-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #64748b;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .series-description {
    max-width: 50rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .series-list article {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .item-number {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #64748b;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }

  h3 a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }

  h3 a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .series-transition {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #64748b;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  .coming-soon {
    color: #64748b;
  }
</style>